From: "K. Y. Srinivasan" <kys@microsoft.com>
Date: Wed, 9 Jul 2014 23:33:46 -0700
Patch-mainline: submitted
Subject: Drivers: scsi: storvsc: Set cmd_per_lun to reflect value supported by
 the Host

Set cmd_per_lun to reflect value supported by the Host.
In this version of the patch I have addressed comments from
Christoph Hellwig <hch@infradead.org>

Signed-off-by: K. Y. Srinivasan <kys@microsoft.com>
Cc: <stable@vger.kernel.org>
Acked-by: <ohering@suse.de>
---
 drivers/scsi/storvsc_drv.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/scsi/storvsc_drv.c b/drivers/scsi/storvsc_drv.c
index bb49109..7289323 100644
--- a/drivers/scsi/storvsc_drv.c
+++ b/drivers/scsi/storvsc_drv.c
@@ -1698,7 +1698,7 @@ static struct scsi_host_template scsi_driver = {
 	.slave_alloc =		storvsc_device_alloc,
 	.slave_destroy =	storvsc_device_destroy,
 	.slave_configure =	storvsc_device_configure,
-	.cmd_per_lun =		1,
+	.cmd_per_lun =		255,
 	.can_queue =		STORVSC_MAX_IO_REQUESTS*STORVSC_MAX_TARGETS,
 	.this_id =		-1,
 	/* no use setting to 0 since ll_blk_rw reset it to 1 */
